# 🚨 ResuAI-Pulse | Next-Gen Emergency Response Dashboard
> **AI-Powered Emergency Dispatch System with Real-time Geospatial Intelligence.**

[![Live Demo](https://img.shields.io/badge/Live-Demo-red?style=for-the-badge&logo=vercel)](https://resuai-pulse.vercel.app)
[![Backend Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/Backend-Online-emerald?style=for-the-badge&logo=fastapi)](https://resuai-backend-api.vercel.app/)

## 🌟 The Problem
During emergencies, every second counts. Traditional systems often suffer from manual dispatch delays, lack of real-time victim location tracking, and poor coordination between different departments (Police, Medical, Fire). **ResuAI-Pulse** solves this by automating the entire pipeline from incident reporting to responder dispatch.

## 🚀 Key Features
- **🤖 AI Intent Classification:** Uses an NLP engine (Logistic Regression) to classify emergency types (Fire, Medical, Accident, Crime) from raw text or voice inputs.
- **📍 Real-time Geospatial Routing:** Automatically fetches the **top 3 nearest hospitals/police stations** using the **Overpass API (OpenStreetMap)**.
- **🛣️ Dynamic Navigation:** Visualizes the shortest path between the victim and the first responder using dashed-polyline routing.
- **📞 Omni-Channel Alerts:** - **Voice Call:** Triggers automated IVR calls to dispatchers via **Twilio Voice API**.
  - **Email:** Sends instant high-priority email alerts via **SMTP**.
- **📱 Responsive Command Center:** A "Mobile-First" dashboard that works perfectly on Desktop (Sidebar view) and Mobile (Floating Chat Widget).
- **🚨 Priority Monitoring:** Visual "Pulse" effect and audio alerts for high-severity (9+) incidents.

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
| Layer | Technologies |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Frontend** | React.js, Tailwind CSS, Leaflet.js, Lucide Icons |
| **Backend** | FastAPI (Python), Uvicorn |
| **AI/ML** | Scikit-learn (NLP), Pydantic |
| **APIs** | Twilio (Voice), Overpass API (Maps), SMTP (Email) |
| **Deployment** | Vercel (Serverless Functions) |

## 🏗️ System Architecture
1. **User Input:** Victim reports an incident via text or quick-action buttons.
2. **AI Processing:** FastAPI backend analyzes the threat level and severity.
3. **Spatial Query:** System fetches the 3 closest emergency nodes based on live GPS coordinates.
4. **Automated Dispatch:** Parallel triggers for Twilio Voice Calls and Email Notifications.
5. **Dashboard Update:** Real-time log update and Map routing for the Command Center.

